benefits, great pay,

01:40:12.660 --> 01:40:13.960
all that kind of stuff."

01:40:13.960 --> 01:40:17.400
And I looked it up, and sure
enough, it was 4.6 years,

01:40:17.400 --> 01:40:18.820
was the average turnover
at Boeing,

01:40:18.820 --> 01:40:21.650
which I found kind of amazing.

01:40:21.650 --> 01:40:26.590
But the design -- talking
about the need for archival

01:40:26.590 --> 01:40:29.410
in the A&amp;D industry,
look at the B52.

01:40:29.410 --> 01:40:33.450
The design of that
started in the late '40s.

01:40:33.450 --> 01:40:36.090
We're still flying it today.

01:40:36.090 --> 01:40:39.180
I don't really see it
going away anytime soon.

01:40:39.180 --> 01:40:45.800
And we have other commercial
and defense products that are

01:40:45.800 --> 01:40:49.780
in that same life
cycle, 707 as example.

01:40:49.780 --> 01:40:52.080
They're still flying.

01:40:57.610 --> 01:41:00.630
From the collaboration
standpoint, Boeing has --

01:41:00.630 --> 01:41:02.880
are a lot of companies --

01:41:02.880 --> 01:41:05.640
and it's not just an
aerospace thing, obviously.

01:41:05.640 --> 01:41:07.400
I mean, look at BMW.

01:41:07.400 --> 01:41:11.830
They make cars all over the
world, and oddly enough,

01:41:11.830 --> 01:41:14.950
the largest BMW manufacturing
facility is

01:41:14.950 --> 01:41:16.870
in South Carolina, where I live.

01:41:16.870 --> 01:41:20.660
And I heard that, and I was
going, "That's just amazing.

01:41:20.660 --> 01:41:24.150
The largest BMW facility in the
world is in South Carolina."

01:41:24.150 --> 01:41:29.210
But Boeing's a 24-hour operation
due to their global nature.

01:41:29.210 --> 01:41:34.380
They have hundreds of partners,
and we use the term partner

01:41:34.380 --> 01:41:38.330
to mean like a Pratt
&amp; Whitney, or a GE,

01:41:38.330 --> 01:41:40.620
or a Rockwell, or a Honeywell.

01:41:40.620 --> 01:41:43.090
And then they also have
thousands upon thousands

01:41:43.090 --> 01:41:44.500
of suppliers, you know,

01:41:44.500 --> 01:41:47.340
that they may make one
little bracket or something.

01:41:47.340 --> 01:41:53.680
So anyway, there's certainly a
need for kind of a standard way

01:41:53.680 --> 01:41:56.970
of communicating among all
these partners and suppliers,

01:41:56.970 --> 01:41:59.360
due to the global
nature of Boeing.

01:41:59.360 --> 01:42:05.910
So in steps the LOTAR project
here, and actually, this is kind

01:42:05.910 --> 01:42:08.490
