02:56:34.830 --> 02:56:38.750
We haven't had, I don't think,
a new building go all the way

02:56:38.750 --> 02:56:40.400
through using BIM
for the entire thing,

02:56:40.400 --> 02:56:42.340
and now we're solely
using that model

02:56:42.340 --> 02:56:44.180
to then manage the building.

02:56:44.180 --> 02:56:46.290
I think that over
the last 10 years,

02:56:46.290 --> 02:56:49.000
we have gotten more advanced
in what we're using BIM for,

02:56:49.000 --> 02:56:51.380
and we have had projects
take BIM all the way

02:56:51.380 --> 02:56:53.210
through design, through
construction.

02:56:53.210 --> 02:56:56.590
And you have a fairly
good dem model at the end,

02:56:56.590 --> 02:56:58.960
but the issue still that I
have, and that the agency has,

02:56:58.960 --> 02:57:01.900
is that -- you know,
maintaining that BIM model

02:57:01.900 --> 02:57:04.220
with all the small
projects that happen in it,

02:57:04.220 --> 02:57:07.600
or happen to the building after
