02:57:10.260 --> 02:57:13.320
aren't -- don't have experience
doing that, so we'd have

02:57:13.320 --> 02:57:14.620
to hire contractors to do it.

02:57:14.620 --> 02:57:15.980
So I think the maintenance
of that model

02:57:15.980 --> 02:57:22.990
through after the project still
becomes a huge issue for us.

02:57:22.990 --> 02:57:26.080
&gt;&gt; Kristine Fallon: Well, I
think, on that, we've done a lot

02:57:26.080 --> 02:57:30.900
of studies for organizations
who wanted to get into some kind

02:57:30.900 --> 02:57:36.410
